---
description: Cursor-based pagination & bulk for large datasets.
globs:
  - src/**/*
alwaysApply: true
---

Rules:
- Use cursor pagination: `first/after` (forward) and `last/before` (back). Always select `pageInfo { hasNextPage hasPreviousPage startCursor endCursor }`.
- Treat cursors as opaque; never decode.
- Max per page 250; for large exports use Admin GraphQL bulk operations.
- Reset cursors when filters/sort/search changes; persist cursor state in URL if the UI supports back/forward.

Code hint:
- Create a typed paginateConnection<T>() helper that returns nodes, pageInfo, and next/prev helpers.